## File Organization & Conventions

### Directory Structure
```
TING/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router pages and API routes
├── components/       # React components (screen, utility, layout)
├── db/              # Database schema and migrations
├── lib/             # Core business logic
│   ├── bot/         # Bot engine modules (AI, prompts, flows)
│   └── nurture/     # Nurture system modules
├── tests/           # Test suites (api, critical, e2e, unit, evals)
├── docs/            # Documentation and plans
├── scripts/         # Utility scripts
├── public/          # Static assets
├── reports/         # Generated reports
├── .github/         # GitHub Actions workflows
└── [config files]   # Project configuration
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Files**: kebab-case (e.g., `ai-bot.ts`, `whatsapp.ts`, `leadStateMachine.ts`)
- **Directories**: kebab-case (e.g., `lib/bot`, `app/api`)
- **API routes**: snake_case with folder structure (e.g., `api/leads/route.ts`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `InboxScreen.tsx`, `Topbar.tsx`)
- **Tests**: snake_case with `.spec.ts` extension (e.g., `bot.spec.ts`, `leadStateMachine.spec.ts`)
- **Migrations**: Numbered with description (e.g., `01_data_safety.sql`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `GROQ_MODEL`, `REGISTER_IP_LIMIT`)

### Code Style
- **Function names**: camelCase (e.g., `handleAiBotMessage`, `waSendText`)
- **Types/Interfaces**: PascalCase (e.g., `BotStage`, `AIDecision`)
- **Private functions**: camelCase with underscore prefix (e.g., `_supabase`)
- **Comments**: JSDoc style for public APIs

### File Size Patterns
- **Largest files**:
  - `lib/ai-bot.ts` (495 lines) - Bot orchestrator
  - `app/page.tsx` (430 lines) - Landing page
  - `components/screens/PropertiesScreen.tsx` (50KB)
  - `components/screens/InboxScreen.tsx` (44KB)
  - `components/screens/LeadsScreen.tsx` (30KB)

### Testing Coverage
- **Unit tests**: ~50 individual test files for pure functions
- **E2E tests**: 6 test suites covering critical flows
- **Eval tests**: Engine evaluation scenarios (scenarios.ts)
- **Total**: 70+ test files with comprehensive coverage

